description: This trap indicates that a bundle link mismatch has
been detected. The following objects are reported:
mfrBundleNearEndName: configured name of near end bundle
mfrBundleLinkNearEndName: configured name of near end bundle
mfrBundleLinkFarEndName: reported name of far end bundle
Note: that the configured items may have been configured
Note: The mfrBundleLinkMismatch counter is incremented when
objects.test: $SNMPTRAPCMD FR-MFR-MIB::mfrMibTrapBundleLinkMismatch FR-MFR-MIB::mfrBundleNearEndName s EXAMPLE FR-MFR-MIB::mfrBundleFarEndName s EXAMPLE FR-MFR-MIB::mfrBundleLinkNearEndName s EXAMPLE FR-MFR-MIB::mfrBundleLinkFarEndName s EXAMPLE FR-MFR-MIB::mfrBundleLinkFarEndBundleName s EXAMPLE

description: The configured name of the bundle.
variables.name: FR-MFR-MIB::mfrBundleNearEndName

description: Name of the bundle received from the far end.
variables.name: FR-MFR-MIB::mfrBundleFarEndName

description: The configured bundle link name that is sent to the far end.
variables.name: FR-MFR-MIB::mfrBundleLinkNearEndName

description: Name of bundle link received from far end.
variables.name: FR-MFR-MIB::mfrBundleLinkFarEndName

description: Name of far end bundle for this link received from far end.
variables.name: FR-MFR-MIB::mfrBundleLinkFarEndBundleName
